1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
Some creatures deceive to survive.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:02,400
How?

3
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:06,000
Meet Batesian mimicry, where harmless species imitate dangerous ones.

4
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:08,800
This strategy confuses predators, increasing survival chances.

5
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:13,200
Take the viceroy butterfly; it resembles the toxic monarch, tricking birds.

6
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,200
But is all mimicry effective?

7
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,600
Not always—environment plays a key role.

8
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,600
Want more mind-bending nature facts?

9
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,400
Hit follow!
